cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image matting, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of manifold learning methods also suggests a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The optimization techniques used in the paper may also make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of subspace reconstructing error suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
